Prefix Sum-> It is a concept of taking sum of all the previous elements in an arrayand putting it at that particular index.3586213816222425-> This technique is useful in many type of leetcode questions wherethings like max sum of subarrays or split arrays is asked.Example: Daily Que 1st Jan 2025- 1422. Maximum Score After Splitting a string"011101"0 1 1 1 0 1left -> 0right -> 11101score -> zeros in left + ones in rightscore = 1+4 = 50 1 1 1 0 1left -> 01right -> 1101score -> zeros in left + ones in rightscore = 1+3 = 4-> score = 0(L) + 1(R) score = 0(L) + (1(T) -1(L)) score = 0(L) - 1(L) + 1(T)Now 1(T) is a constant(0(L) - 1(L)) is variable score = best(0(L) - 1(L)) + 1(T)Now we can just iterate from the left and calculate the number of onesand zerosCode:import mathclass Solution: def maxScore(self, s: str) -> int: ones = 0 zeros = 0 best = -math.inf for i in range(len(s) - 1): if s[i] == '0': zeros += 1 else: ones += 1 best = max(best, zeros - ones) if s[-1] == '1': ones += 1 return ones + best- We need to explicitly check for 1 in the last index because both the leftand the right section of the string cannot be empty so they at least needone character.- after calculating the best zeros(left)-ones(right) we add it to the totalno. of ones to get the best score possible and return it.
